      <br>Caster's Realm has put up some screenshots of the new interface.  I have to say, though it reminds me of the interface from DAoC in a way, it looks easier to work with.  To see the new screenshots, click <a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/screenshots2/default.asp?category=14">here</a>.<br><br>Sony also posted some screenshots of this new interface on their website.  To view those, click <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/interface/">here</a>.<br><br>And if THAT is not enough to satisfy your need for the new interface that includes:<br><br><blockquot>- Item Inspection: Alt-Leftclick now pops up the inspect box and keeps it there.<br><br>- Quantity Selection: You can now type numbers when referring to stackable items and coins.<br><br>- Key Mapper: Every top level window still has a hotkey you can use to open and close it, and all of the keys can still be remapped through the Options screeen. (The hex nut icon in the window selector, or Alt-O by default). To turn the window selector itself on and off, the default key is Alt-W.<br><br>- Mousewheel: ...should automatically work in every UI screen that has a scroll bar. (including Chat, Merchants, Looting, etc.)<br><br>* For those interested in developing custom skins for the interface:<br><br>You'll notice that there is now a directory called UIFiles beneath your EverQuest install directory. <br><br>The default skin (aka "The New UI") is stored in the directory called, predictably "default," and we've included a document called "AboutSIDL.doc" in the UIFiles directory.<br><br>If you make yourself a new skin, please create a separate directory for it in the UIFiles directory. Once the skin is in there, you can switch to it by typing "/loadskin <directory_name>"<br><br>Working with the skins at this point is not an activity for the faint of heart, but if you're inclined to hack around in those files, AboutSIDL will hopefully help out a bit.</blockquote><br>You can check it out for yourself now on the Test server.<br><br></font></p>
